Ghana Currency Strengthens as Investors Bought Cedi Securities

-- B y   M o s e s   M o z a r t   D z a w u
-- 
2011-05-12T15:39:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-12/ghana-currency-strengthens-as-investors-bought-cedi-securities.html
Ghana ’s currency, the cedi,
strengthened as foreign investors sold dollars to buy securities
priced in the local denomination.  The currency of the world’s second biggest cocoa producer
traded at 1.5078 per dollar as of 3 p.m. in the capital, Accra,
from a close of 1.5090 yesterday  “The market today received dollar inflows from investors
living abroad, either to buy shares or bonds,” Kevin Adarkwa, a
currency trader at the local unit of Standard Chartered Bank
Plc, said in a telephone interview today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 